{
  "stem": "10818.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I later on went to my grandparents' house, I saw part of the mob coming on the other side-- or on the same side.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I crossed over and quickly walked the other way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But well, we-- we-- I told you about how we listened to the radio that night and, and-- to see what the foreign radio would say.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were reporting it, but they were-- and-- and then we realized it was taking place all over Germany, of course.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After my father came home from Frankfurt, he had seen it in, in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we suddenly realized that it was totally organized and was taking place all over the place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the next day was a Friday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And on Friday nights, we always went to my grandparents' for dinner and shabbat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- now I have to say few words about my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My grandmother had three sons.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And two of them were killed in the first World War.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So my father was the only survivor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She never got over this, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She and my father were very, very close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] to get back to what happened the next day, the, the knock on-- the famous knock on the door.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the Gestapo was there and said to my father to come along.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So my father threw a few things in a suitcase and came-- and, and wrote on the back of an English language teaching book, you know, notify the cousins in America immediately.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Whatever they can do.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "This is no, no more time to say depression or what have you in America.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You know, we've got to have a way of getting out of this country immediately.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And, and they took him along.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
